{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "To enhance the conversational abilities of a LLM for answering business process-related tasks, we propose to adopt a process-aware Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) framework in conjunction with fine-tuning.",
    "This strategy can leverage fine-tuning to extend process-and domain-specific structural and behavioral knowledge leaving the RAG in charge of incorporating the contextual knowledge related to the specific user requests.",
    "The overall system, called Business Process LLM (BPLLM), fine-tuned on a specific process model (different process model formats are evaluated), supports the user in a wide range of process comprehension and execution tasks using natural language.",
    "In the proposed framework, a LLaMA 2 [7] LLM is combined with a variant of RAG [8] [7] tailored to deal with the specific aspects of the structural and behavioral representation of business processes.",
    "Moreover, a process-aware chunking approach [9] along with a suitable prompting strategy is included."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In the proposed framework, a LLaMA 2 [7] LLM is combined with a variant of RAG [8] [7] tailored to deal with the specific aspects of the structural and behavioral representation of business processes.",
    "Moreover, a process-aware chunking approach [9] along with a suitable prompting strategy is included."
  ]
}